Ooni of Ife Oba Adeyeye Ogunwusi has installed a socialite, businesswoman and philanthropist Dr Toyin Kolade as Iyalaje of Oodua. The installation took place at the weekend at the Palace of the traditional ruler. The monarch urged her to work more for the promotion of Yoruba culture and tradition. Kolade described her installation as a divine call to duty. She promised to continue to work for the prosperity of the Oduduwa race. She also called for cooperation that would enhance trade and commerce among the people of the race.